<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Neat1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Neat,</orth> subst. horned cattle: <cit><quote>the steer, the heifer and the calf are all called n.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 125</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a lion in a herd of n.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what say you to a --'s foot?</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 17</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you dried --'s tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.271" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 271</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 112</bibl>. <cit><quote>--'s leather,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 73</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 29</bibl>.*
